723741f-a.title: Manhattan: Varick Street - Watts Street
723741f-a.text:
93-73 Varick Street, west side, from Watts to Canal Streets, the block which is to be demolished early in 1929, showing also 431 Canal Street, at the N.. corner of Varick Street. No. 93, on the corner at the right, and No. 89, are frame houses with a brick facing. No. 431 Canal Street has no Varick Street house number.
June, 1925.
Brown Brothers.

723740f-a.title: Manhattan: Varick Street - Watts Street
723740f-a.text:
Varick Street, north from, but not including, Watts Street. The first factory on the east side north of the Spring Street Church, whose side and rear is shown, is the Stanley & Patterson Building (about 1928), ocoupying the block from Spring to Vandam Streets.
March 20, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
